laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.

findings.liver: Homogeneously hypodense, consistent with hepatic steatosis.
findings.spleen: Multiple perisplenic varices with evidence of a splenorenal shunt. Normal size and attenuation throughout.
findings.kidneys: Multiple hypodense cysts in bilateral kidneys; the largest cyst in the right kidney measures 6.2 x 5.6 cm.
findings.appendix: Prominent, measuring up to 9 mm in diameter, with possible minimal hyperemia of the wall.
